        text: 'Option C',
      },
    ],
    comment: '<p>Declaring each transition property individually can be intensive, especially using <code>vendor prefixes</code>.</p>\n<p>Instead, try the shorthand property <code>transition</code> that supports all the different values.</p>\n<p>Using only this alone it is possible to set every transition value in order of <code>transition-property</code>, <code>transition-duration</code>, <code>transition-timing-function</code>, and lastly <code>transition-delay</code>.</p>\n<pre><code class="language-css">.box {\n  background: #2db34a;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  transition: background .2s linear;\n}\n.box:hover {\n  background: #ff7b29;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>For setting many transitions at once, set every individual group of transition values, then use a comma to separate each group of additional ones.</p>\n',
  },
